{"title": "G-7 summit: Can Ukraine President Zelensky\u2019s appearance stiffen resolve to punish Russia?", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2023-05-20", "content": "HIROSHIMA, Japan \u2013 The first city to experience the horrors of an atomic bomb, 78 years ago, is set to welcome the leader of a country facing the same nuclear threat.\nUkrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky will attend the ongoing summit of the Group of Seven (G-7) bloc of wealthy democracies in person on Sunday, according to reports, in a bid to stiffen their resolve to further punish Russia for its invasion of his country and which has also threatened the use of nuclear weapons."}